helptext sub_stn_150_help =
 "
 **** SUB STATION 150 POPUP MIMIC ****
 ------------------------------------------------- -------------------------------------------------
T5 Bulk Supply Point Substation 150 
 ------------------------------------------------- -------------------------------------------------
The primary function of the T5 Bulk Supply Point Substation 150 is to provide
33 kV supplies to primary substations 151 and 152, Heathrow Central and West Intake.

This Mimic displays circuit breaker status, current and voltage for Panels on new Substation 150.


HV Mimic

The Circuit Breakers are Control and Monitoring. 
Incomers are Monitoring only. All other circuit breakers provide control.

The Analogue meters display high and low alarms together with under/over/invalid ranges.
Low and High alarms may be set by the operator. The meter can also be tagged.

Maximum Demand meters are also shown (display only)


LV Mimic Popup
Substation 150 houses 2 off 11/0.415kV transformers for the supply of local equipment via an LV switchboard.
The statuses of the local transformers and the LV ACBs are displayed via the LV popup mimic.

As substation 150 is a 33kV substation, the local transformers receive 11kV incoming voltage from the following
sources:-
Local TX1   Sub 152
Local TX2   Sub 10


References:
------------------
Operation and Maintenance Manual 	- 

Keypages from the Mimic Menu Object -  for information on mimic objects used (HV Area)
 ------------------

 "